<div id="about-the-community" class="section-spacer">
    <h2 class="sect-title">About MacEwan Glen</h2>
    <div class="col-grid-2">
        <div>
            <p class="par-lg">Although, the development of the community began in the early eighties, it has only recently been wrapped up.</p>

            <p class="par-lg">Named after the Lieutenant Governor of Alberta and the Mayor of Calgary, John Walter Grant MacEwan, the community in MacEwan Glen is a mature neighborhood that majorly comprises of single-family detached homes with the exception of a few half-duplexes and townhomes scattered around. </p>

            <p class="par-lg">A typical single family home in MacEwan Glen Real Estate can be purchased at an average price of $450,000. Residents in the community have abundant opportunities for recreation in the Nosehill Park, which is also one among Canadaâ€™s largest municipal reserves. </p>

